Cousins is lucky if he can step into his throws with confidence. He's just not the guy to put a team over the top, and he's currently in his "prime". What a letdown he must be for Vikes fans, knowing he'll pretty much suck whenever you need him not to suck the most. Dude is super mediocre

snippet.textDisplay:
Vikings O-Line was just atrocious. The defense showed up and got tired at the end.

Packers still have a lot of work to do. Those fumbles and turn overs would have cost them the game with any other team that's in the play offs. Don't have the Packers winning their first playoff game, let alone go to the SB. Even if they do, they're not ready to face a team like Baltimore.

Only two teams I can see beating Baltimore are the Saints, Seahawks, or the 49ers.
